<item>
            <title>[CODEC-68] isBase64 throws ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException on some non-BASE64 bytes</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CODEC-68</link>
                <project id="12310464" key="CODEC">Commons Codec</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;the following code throws an ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException although it is perfectly valid (the byte 0x9c should be ignored according to the standard):&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;byte&lt;/span&gt;[x] = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;byte&lt;/span&gt;[] { &apos;n&apos;, &apos;A&apos;, &apos;=&apos;, &apos;=&apos;, 0x9c };
Base64.decodeBase64(x);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The problem is the following method:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;private&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;static&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;boolean&lt;/span&gt; isBase64(&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;byte&lt;/span&gt; octect) {
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (octect == PAD) {
            &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;;
        } &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;else&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (base64Alphabet[octect] == -1) {
            &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;false&lt;/span&gt;;
        } &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;else&lt;/span&gt; {
            &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;;
        }
    }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;in Java octect is a &lt;b&gt;signed&lt;/b&gt; value, so it is not correct to use it as an offset for an array &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;0..254&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; which base64Alphabet is. 0x9c is -100!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;FIX:&lt;br/&gt;
use base64Alphabet[ 0xff &amp;amp; octect ] in the &quot;else if&quot; block to convert the octet prior using it as an offset for the lookup table&lt;/p&gt;</description>
